### Define Basic Agent Configuration

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/extensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md

Sets up agents with essential properties like model and prompt. Demonstrates agents with only a model, only a prompt, or both.

```prose
# Define a research agent
agent researcher:
  model: sonnet
  prompt: "You are a research assistant skilled at finding and synthesizing information"

# Define a writing agent
agent writer:
  model: opus
  prompt: "You are a technical writer who creates clear, concise documentation"

# Agent with only model
agent quick:
  model: haiku

# Agent with only prompt
agent expert:
  prompt: "You are a domain expert"

# Agent with skills
agent web-researcher:
  model: sonnet
  skills: ["web-search", "summarizer"]

# Agent with permissions
agent file-handler:
  permissions:
    read: ["*.md", "*.txt"]
    write: ["output/"]
    bash: deny
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Sub-agent Tool Access and Concurrency

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/tools/subagents.md

This JSON5 configuration snippet demonstrates how to define default sub-agent concurrency and explicitly allow or deny tools for sub-agents. The 'deny' list takes precedence over the 'allow' list.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      subagents: {
        maxConcurrent: 1
      }
    }
  },
  tools: {
    subagents: {
      tools: {
        // deny wins
        deny: ["gateway", "cron"],
        // if allow is set, it becomes allow-only (deny still wins)
        // allow: ["read", "exec", "process"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Local Models Only Configuration

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/configuration-examples.md

Sets up Openclaw to use only local models, specifically configuring the LM Studio provider. It defines the primary model and details for the local provider.

```json5
{
  "agent": {
    "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace",
    "model": { "primary": "lmstudio/minimax-m2.1-gs32" }
  },
  "models": {
    "mode": "merge",
    "providers": {
      "lmstudio": {
        "baseUrl": "http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1",
        "apiKey": "lmstudio",
        "api": "openai-responses",
        "models": [
          {
            "id": "minimax-m2.1-gs32",
            "name": "MiniMax M2.1 GS32",
            "reasoning": false,
            "input": ["text"],
            "cost": { "input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0 },
            "contextWindow": 196608,
            "maxTokens": 8192
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Sub-Agent Defaults

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/configuration.md

Sets default configurations for spawned sub-agents, including the default model, maximum concurrent runs, and auto-archiving settings. It also defines per-subagent tool policies.

```json5
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "subagents": {
        "model": {
          "primary": "default-model",
          "fallbacks": ["fallback-model-1", "fallback-model-2"]
        },
        "maxConcurrent": 5,
        "archiveAfterMinutes": 30,
        "tools": {
          "subagents": {
            "tools": {
              "allow": ["tool1", "tool2"],
              "deny": ["tool3"]
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
